# Brain — Personal Context (example)

Copy this to `context.md` and customize for your own setup. The Brain loads this as background context
for AI calls, so it knows who you are and how you want to communicate.

## About me
- Name: [Your name]
- Role: [Founder / Operator / Advisor / etc.]
- Company: [Your venture]

## Ventures & Contacts
- **[Venture 1]**: [One-line description, key people]
- **[Venture 2]**: [One-line description, key people]
- **Lawyer**: [Name, firm, when to use formal tone]

## Writing Style
- [Direct / formal / casual / etc.]
- [Avoid filler words like "actually", "basically"]
- [Language preference: English / German / both]

## Email Conventions
- To [contact group A]: Formal address, Sir/Madam
- To [contact group B]: Informal, first-name basis
- Sign-off: [Best / Cheers / Mit besten Gruessen / etc.]

## Known Projects (the Brain may search these)
- [Project name]: [Drive folder / repo / Notion page]
- [Project name]: [Drive folder / repo / Notion page]
